==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Arrogation
<hw>Ar`ro*ga"tion</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>arrogatio</ets>, fr. <ets>arrogare</ets>. Cf.
<er>Adrogation</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of arrogating, or
making exorbitant claims; the act of taking more than one is justly
entitled to.</def> <rj><au>Hall.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Civ. Law)</fld> <def>Adoption of a person of full
age.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Arrogative</ent>⟦br⟧
